In this proclamation, President Donald J. Trump declares October 2017 as National Disability Employment Awareness Month. He emphasizes the importance of recognizing and celebrating the contributions of American workers with disabilities and their skills in the workplace. He acknowledges the challenges faced by individuals with disabilities in finding employment opportunities and expresses the goal of promoting their independence, economic self-sufficiency, pride, and community through employment. The President directs the Department of Labor, the Social Security Administration, and other federal agencies to identify effective strategies to help people stay at work or return to work after becoming disabled. He also highlights the commitment to providing all Americans, including those with disabilities, with opportunities to gain the skills needed for 21st-century jobs. The President calls upon government and labor leaders, employers, and the American people to recognize National Disability Employment Awareness Month through appropriate programs, ceremonies, and activities.